lsgeber, Vermittler und Helfer zu. Anhand von sechs Berliner Fallstudien untersucht Düring aus der Perspektive von Helfern und Hilfsempfängern die soziale Verfasstheit von Hilfsbereitschaft.   aWhy did people help Jews hide from the Nazis? This study examines interactions between helpers and aid recipients using the methods of social network research. Based on six Berlin case studies, the author looks at the social determinants for willingness to help, trust formation, network effects, and the daily practice of providing help from the perspectives of helpers and aid recipients.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aBusiness networks. 0aStrategic alliances (Business). 4aBerlin. 4aDigital Humanities. 4aHilfeverhalten. 4aHistorische Netzwerkforschung. 4aHolocaust. 4aJuden. 4aNational Socialism. 4aNationalsozialismus. 4adigital humanities. 4ahelping behavior. 4ahistorical network research. 7aHISTORY / Holocaust.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2015z9783110438727oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831103967750 cprintz978311037466740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311036894940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110368949423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110368949.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2015  aZDB-23-DGGb2015